article.description: — MJ Randolph had a career-high 27 points as Florida A&M beat Austin Peay 76-70 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Randolph carries Florida A&M past Austin Peay 76-70
article.linkText: Randolph carries Florida A&M past Austin Peay 76-70
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- — MJ Randolph had a career-high 27 points as Florida A&M beat Austin Peay 76-70 on Tuesday night. Evins Desir had 12 points for Florida A&M (1-4). Jai Clark and Johnny Brown each added 11 points. Mike Peake had 18 points and seven rebounds for the Governors (4-3). Terry Taylor added 13 points and eight rebounds. Reginald Gee had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
